Greek Stocks: Alapis Holdings, Hellenic Exchanges Move in Athens

-- B y   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-03-09T12:59:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/greek-stocks-alapis-holdings-hellenic-exchanges-move-in-athens.html
  Greece ’s benchmark ASE Index added
25.73, or 1.7 percent, to 1,551.23 at 2:45 p.m. in  Athens ,
paring a 3.8 percent drop yesterday.  The FTSE/ASE 20 Index of the country’s biggest companies
advanced 2.5 percent to 716.74. The Cypriot General Index gained
3.4 percent to 1,014.78.  The following shares were the most active in Athens trading
today. Symbols are in parentheses.  Alapis Holdings SA (ALAPIS GA) dropped 22 percent to 36
cents, on course for its biggest one day decline since 2008. The
Greek drugmaker plans a 98.1 million euro ($136.3 million) share
capital increase and the issue of two convertible bonds of as
much as 300 million euros, euro2day.gr reported. Separately, the
Athens-based company said it hired Lazard & Co Ltd. as a
financial adviser on its  capital structure .  Hellenic Exchanges SA (EXAE GA) rose 5 percent to 6.30
euros, snapping a five day fall. Foreign investors raised their
share of stocks listed on the Greek exchange to 51.2 percent in
February from 49 percent in the same month a year earlier,
according to an e-mailed statement from the operator of the
Athens bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Weeks in Athens at 
 nweeks2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  David Merritt  at 
 dmerritt1@bloomberg.net  